Interface ISchematicsManager

public interface ISchematicsManager
Manager for the server's schematic registry.

ISchematicsManager exposes a read-only view of the in-memory registry of schematics that have been pasted into the world via the /schematic load command. External plugins can query which schematics are loaded, in which worlds, and which block locations they occupy.

Typical usage

ISchematicsManager schematics = ProudCoreAPI.get().getSchematicsManager();

// Check if an arena schematic is already pasted
if (schematics.isLoaded("arena_1", "world")) {
    List<Location> blocks = schematics.getBlocks("arena_1", "world");
    // ... do something with the block list
}

// List all loaded schematics
for (String name : schematics.getAllNames()) {
    System.out.println("Loaded: " + name);
}

  • Method Details

    • isLoaded

      boolean isLoaded(String name, String worldName)
      Returns true if the schematic with the given name is currently registered (i.e. has been pasted) in the specified world.
      Parameters:
      name - schematic identifier (filename without .schem)
      worldName - the target world name
      Returns:
      true if loaded, false otherwise

    • getBlocks

      List<org.bukkit.Location> getBlocks(String name, String worldName)
      Returns an unmodifiable list of all block Locations that were placed when the schematic was pasted, or an empty list if it is not registered.

      This list can be used, for example, to iterate over arena boundaries or to verify that a structure is still intact.

      Parameters:
      name - schematic identifier
      worldName - the target world name
      Returns:
      unmodifiable list of block locations; never null

    • getNamesInWorld

      Set<String> getNamesInWorld(String worldName)
      Returns the set of schematic names currently loaded in the given world.
      Parameters:
      worldName - the target world name
      Returns:
      an unmodifiable set of schematic names; never null, may be empty

    • getAllNames

      Set<String> getAllNames()
      Returns all registered schematic names across all worlds.

      If the same schematic name has been loaded in multiple worlds it will appear only once in the returned set.

      Returns:
      an unmodifiable set of schematic names; never null, may be empty

    • getAllWithWorld

      Map<String,String> getAllWithWorld()
      Returns a map of every registered schematic keyed by its internal "worldName:schematicName" composite key, with a human-readable display label as the value.

      Useful for admin list commands or GUIs that need both the key for look-up and a pretty label for display.

      Returns:
      an unmodifiable map; never null, may be empty
